data.chText: 扩大，增加，增强（尺码、数量或重要性）
data.enText: to become greater in size, number or importance; to make sth greater in size, number or importance
Metals expand when they are heated.

data.chText: 孩子的词汇量通过阅读得到扩大。
data.enText: A child's vocabulary expands through reading.

data.chText: 腰围可松可紧适合任何尺码。
data.enText: The waist expands to fit all sizes.

data.chText: 呼吸时胸部肌肉使胸廓扩大让空气吸入肺部。
data.enText: In breathing the chest muscles expand the rib cage and allow air to be sucked into the lungs.

data.chText: 新体制扩大了家庭医生的作用。
data.enText: The new system expanded the role of family doctors.

data.chText: 目前尚无扩建地方机场的方案。
data.enText: There are no plans to expand the local airport.
if a business expands or is expanded , new branches are opened, it makes more money, etc.

data.chText: 我们增开了两个商店以扩展业务。
data.enText: We've expanded the business by opening two more stores.
an expanding economy (= with more businesses starting and growing)
to talk more; to add details to what you are saying

data.chText: 我把问题重复了一遍，等着她详细回答。
data.enText: I repeated the question and waited for her to expand.

data.chText: 详述；充分叙述；详细阐明
data.enText: to say more about sth and add some details

data.chText: 请你把这一点详细说明一下好吗？
data.enText: Could you expand on that point, please?

means: 增强(尺码、数量或重要性)

ex.chText: 他通过这种乐器把声音扩大了。
ex.enText: He amplified the sound through the musical instrument.

synonyms.bx: 指放大声音等，尤指音乐声。

ex.chText: 扩大农场/扩建酒店/放大相片
扩大词汇量的一个有效办法就是看报纸。
ex.enText: An effective way to enlarge your vocabulary is to read newspapers.

synonyms.bx: 指放大尺寸、面积、容量等。

ex.chText: 20世纪70年代，该城市的人口迅速增加。
ex.enText: The city's population expanded rapidly in the 1970s.

ex.chText: 古城墙被拆掉，城区被扩大了。
ex.enText: The ancient city walls were demolished and the urban area was expanded.
The number of female students has increased.
They had to increase their investment.

ex.chText: 我们必须增加工业生产。

data.chText: 详述；充分叙述；详细阐明
data.enText: to say more about sth and add some details

data.chText: 请你把这一点详细说明一下好吗？
data.enText: Could you expand on that point, please?

tr: become larger in size or volume or quantity

example: The deer population in this town is thriving
The King extended his rule to the Eastern part of the continent

tr: make bigger or wider in size, volume, or quantity
example: expand the house by adding another wing

tr: add details, as to an account or idea
clarify the meaning of and discourse in a learned way, usually in writing
example: She elaborated on the main ideas in her dissertation

tr: extend in one or more directions

value.def: If something expands or is expanded, it becomes larger.

example.ex: Engineers noticed that the pipes were not expanding as expected...
example.tran: 工程师注意到管道并没有如预期那样膨胀。

example.ex: The money supply expanded by 14.6 per cent in the year to September...
example.tran: 截至9月，当年的货币供应增加了14.6％。

example.ex: We have to expand the size of the image.
example.tran: 我们不得不放大图像的尺寸。

value.def: If something such as a business, organization, or service expands, or if you expand it, it becomes bigger and includes more people, goods, or activities.

example.ex: The popular ceramics industry expanded towards the middle of the 19th century...
example.tran: 到19世纪中期，大众制陶业得到了发展。

example.ex: The interest rate's coming down. I'll be able to expand or stay in business...
example.tran: 利率正在降低，我可以扩大公司或者维持经营。

example.ex: I owned a bookshop and desired to expand the business...
example.tran: 我拥有一家书店，想要扩大业务。

example.ex: Health officials are proposing to expand their services by organising counselling.
example.tran: 卫生官员计划通过组织咨询来扩展他们的服务。
